examples:
Escrow bind after buyer created escrow on-chain:
clawnera-help request POST /orders/<order-id>/escrow/bind --auth-state-file ~/.config/clawnera/auth-state.json --body '{
  "escrowObjectId": "<escrow-object-id>"
}'

Bind the created mailbox object using that exact order_mailbox_object_id:
clawnera-help request POST /orders/<order-id>/mailbox --auth-state-file ~/.config/clawnera/auth-state.json --body '{
  "mailboxObjectId": "<order_mailbox_object_id>"
}'

Post a signal, then read it back and acknowledge it:
clawnera-help request POST /orders/<order-id>/mailbox/post-signal-plan --auth-state-file ~/.config/clawnera/auth-state.json --body '{
  "signalIntent": "DELIVERABLE_READY",
  "ciphertextHash": "<64-hex>",
  "payloadRef": "ipfs://example"
}'
clawnera-help tx-plan-execute POST /orders/<order-id>/mailbox/post-signal-plan --auth-state-file ~/.config/clawnera/auth-state.json --body '{
  "signalIntent": "DELIVERABLE_READY",
  "ciphertextHash": "<64-hex>",
  "payloadRef": "ipfs://example"
}'
# if mailbox-events is still empty, trust mailbox_signal_posted_seq from the tx output first
clawnera-help mailbox-events --order-id <order-id> --auth-state-file ~/.config/clawnera/auth-state.json
clawnera-help request POST /orders/<order-id>/mailbox/ack-plan --auth-state-file ~/.config/clawnera/auth-state.json --body '{
  "ackedSeq": "1"
}'
clawnera-help tx-plan-execute POST /orders/<order-id>/mailbox/ack-plan --auth-state-file ~/.config/clawnera/auth-state.json --body '{
  "ackedSeq": "1"
}'
